d 'RECODE12': module to standardize numeric 1/2 variables and corresponding two-category string variables as labeled 0/1 indicators
d
d  recode12 standardizes eligible numeric variables coded 1/2 and
d eligible two-category string variables as labeled 0/1 indicators.
d For a string variable, the first and second distinct nonmissing
d categories encountered in the current observation order serve as
d source categories 1 and 2. The required yesvalue() option applies
d the same mapping rule to numeric and string variables. The
d command supports numeric-only, string-only, and mixed-variable
d processing; generated-variable and replace modes; user-specified
d suffixes; optional detailed reporting; preservation of missing
d observations; and post-recoding verification. Variables that do
d not satisfy the applicable eligibility rule are left unchanged. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: binary variables
d KW: recoding
d KW: categorical variables
d KW: string variables
d KW: indicator variables
d
d Requires: Stata version 19.5
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260719
d
d Author:  Hao Ma,  NA
d Support: email shouhuoxiwang2027@@gmail.com
d
f recode12.ado
f recode12.sthlp
f recode12_test.do
f recode12_example.do
f recode12_example_data.dta
